@node play "The game: Installation/Playing"

                             Installation

  The installation is very simple, just place "Pivobar" where you
want on your hard drive, floppy disk, Ram Disk, etc. No other files
or Libraries are needed.

NOTE: As I am not sure of this game's 'behaviour' on a stock 68000
      Amiga. For now, until somebody confirms that Pivobar runs
      fine on a 68000 machine, this game will require an Amiga
      with a 68020 or faster processor... sorry!

                             How to play?

  To play, click on any tile on the game board. That tile will
rotate by 90 degrees. However, if the tile is occupied by the
coloured bar and that tile is also in line with one (and only one)
neighbouring tile, the bar will move to the neighbouring tile.

  The goal is to move the coloured bar to the exit tile, which is
represented by a 'pressed down' tile, located at the lower right
position of the game board. Complete the game in the least amount
of moves.

  Have fun!

OPTIONS

  You can change the colour of the coloured bar by clicking on the
'Colour' button.

  You can restart the game any time by clicking on the 'Replay'
button.

  You can quit the game by clicking on the main window's close
button or by pressing on the 'Esc' key.

@endnode

